021/**
022 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#the-audio-element">&lt;audio&gt;</a>
023 * element.
024 *
025 * <p>
026 * The audio element embeds sound content in documents. It can contain audio streams, audio files,
027 * or other audio sources. The browser will choose the most appropriate source based on format
028 * support and user preferences.
029 *
030 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
031 * <p class='bcode w800'>
032 *    // Simple audio with single source
033 *    Audio audio1 = new Audio().src("audio.mp3").controls(true);
034 * 
035 *    // Audio with multiple sources for browser compatibility
036 *    Audio audio2 = new Audio().controls(true)
037 *       .children(
038 *          new Source().src("audio.mp3").type("audio/mpeg"),
039 *          new Source().src("audio.ogg").type("audio/ogg")
040 *       );
041 * 
042 *    // Autoplay audio with loop
043 *    Audio audio3 = new Audio().src("background.mp3").autoplay(true).loop(true).muted(true);
044 * </p>
045 *
046 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
047 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
048 * </ul>
049 */
050@Bean(typeName="audio")
051@FluentSetters
052public class Audio extends HtmlElementContainer {
053
054   /**
055    * Creates an empty {@link Audio} element.
056    */
057   public Audio() {}
058
059   /**
060    * Creates an {@link Audio} element with the specified {@link Audio#src(Object)} attribute.
061    *
062    * @param src The {@link Audio#src(Object)} attribute.
063    */
064   public Audio(String src) {
065      src(src);
066   }
067
068   /**
069    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-autoplay">autoplay</a>
070    * attribute.
071    *
072    * <p>
073    * Hint that the media resource can be started automatically when the page is loaded.
074    *
075    * <p>
076    * This attribute uses deminimized values:
077    * <ul>
078    *    <li><jk>false</jk> - Attribute is not added</li>
079    *    <li><jk>true</jk> - Attribute is added as <js>"autoplay"</js></li>
080    *    <li>Other values - Passed through as-is</li>
081    * </ul>
082    *
083    * @param autoplay
084    *    The new value for this attribute.
085    *    Typically a {@link Boolean} or {@link String}.
086    * @return This object.
087    */
088   public Audio autoplay(Object value) {
089      attr("autoplay", deminimize(value, "autoplay"));
090      return this;
091   }
092
093   /**
094    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-controls">controls</a>
095    * attribute.
096    *
097    * <p>
098    * Show user agent controls.
099    *
100    * <p>
101    * This attribute uses deminimized values:
102    * <ul>
103    *    <li><jk>false</jk> - Attribute is not added</li>
104    *    <li><jk>true</jk> - Attribute is added as <js>"controls"</js></li>
105    *    <li>Other values - Passed through as-is</li>
106    * </ul>
107    *
108    * @param controls
109    *    The new value for this attribute.
110    *    Typically a {@link Boolean} or {@link String}.
111    * @return This object.
112    */
113   public Audio controls(Object value) {
114      attr("controls", deminimize(value, "controls"));
115      return this;
116   }
117
118   /**
119    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-crossorigin">crossorigin</a>
120    * attribute.
121    *
122    * <p>
123    * Specifies how the element handles cross-origin requests for CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing).
124    *
125    * <p>
126    * Possible values:
127    * <ul>
128    *    <li><js>"anonymous"</js> - Cross-origin requests are made without credentials</li>
129    *    <li><js>"use-credentials"</js> - Cross-origin requests include credentials</li>
130    * </ul>
131    *
132    * @param crossorigin How to handle cross-origin requests.
133    * @return This object.
134    */
135   public Audio crossorigin(String value) {
136      attr("crossorigin", value);
137      return this;
138   }
139
140   /**
141    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-loop">loop</a> attribute.
142    *
143    * <p>
144    * Causes the media to automatically restart from the beginning when it reaches the end.
145    *
146    * @param loop If <jk>true</jk>, the media will loop continuously.
147    * @return This object.
148    */
149   public Audio loop(Object value) {
150      attr("loop", value);
151      return this;
152   }
153
154   /**
155    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-mediagroup">mediagroup</a>
156    * attribute.
157    *
158    * <p>
159    * Groups multiple media elements together so they can be controlled as a single unit. All media elements
160    * with the same mediagroup value will share the same MediaController, allowing synchronized playback.
161    *
162    * <p>
163    * This is useful for creating synchronized audio/video presentations or multiple audio tracks.
164    *
165    * @param mediagroup The name of the media group to join.
166    * @return This object.
167    */
168   public Audio mediagroup(String value) {
169      attr("mediagroup", value);
170      return this;
171   }
172
173   /**
174    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-muted">muted</a>
175    * attribute.
176    *
177    * <p>
178    * Mutes the audio output by default. Useful for autoplay videos where audio should be disabled initially.
179    *
180    * @param muted If <jk>true</jk>, the media will be muted by default.
181    * @return This object.
182    */
183   public Audio muted(Object value) {
184      attr("muted", value);
185      return this;
186   }
187
188   /**
189    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-preload">preload</a>
190    * attribute.
191    *
192    * <p>
193    * Specifies how the browser should load the media resource.
194    *
195    * <p>
196    * Possible values:
197    * <ul>
198    *    <li><js>"none"</js> - Do not preload the media</li>
199    *    <li><js>"metadata"</js> - Preload only metadata (duration, dimensions, etc.)</li>
200    *    <li><js>"auto"</js> - Preload the entire media file (default)</li>
201    * </ul>
202    *
203    * @param preload How much of the media to preload.
204    * @return This object.
205    */
206   public Audio preload(Object value) {
207      attr("preload", value);
208      return this;
209   }
210
211   /**
212    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/embedded-content-0.html#attr-media-src">src</a> attribute.
213    *
214    * <p>
215    * Address of the resource.
216    *
217    * <p>
218    * The value can be of any of the following types: {@link URI}, {@link URL}, {@link String}.
219    * Strings must be valid URIs.
220    *
221    * <p>
222    * URIs defined by {@link UriResolver} can be used for values.
223    *
224    * @param src
225    *    The new value for this attribute.
226    *    Typically a {@link URL} or {@link String}.
227    * @return This object.
228    */
229   public Audio src(Object value) {
230      attrUri("src", value);
231      return this;
232   }
